    "headerDoc": "STEP 968 — Ramsey Theory: Exhaustive Computational Proofs (revised)\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-21\n\n  Native_decide proofs for small Ramsey-type numbers.\n\n  Schur convention used here: S(r) = largest n s.t. {1,...,n} admits a\n  sum-free r-coloring (Wikipedia/standard convention).\n  Then S(r)+1 = smallest n s.t. every r-coloring of {1,...,n}\n  has a monochromatic Schur triple.\n\n  Known values:\n     S(1) = 1, S(2) = 4, S(3) = 13, S(4) = 44, S(5) = 160.\n\n  EGZ constant: E(ℤ_n) = 2n-1 = smallest m s.t. every length-m sequence\n  in ℤ_n has a length-n subsequence summing to 0.\n\n  Peace Axiom #196: immutable: tru"
